locality: Bois du Sud. End of side road SE from Noumea-Yate Road, near stream and picnic area.

Parc Riviere Bleu. Maquis near Riviere Bleu just beyond where road crosses the river heading upstream. Vegetation dense and of low stature, 3-8 m tall trees and shrubs. Lots of Proteaceae, Myrtaceae, Epacridaceae, Cunoniaceae and Casurinaceae. Ground cover of Cyperaceae and lichens over porous-rocky, red soil.
Route de Yate: Col de Mouirange.

Mt. Koghis Park. From Auberge to La Cascade. Vegetation variable and includes: tall humid forest especially near Auberge and in valleys, stunted forest on rocky soils, and maquis especially on ridges and where there is evidence of recent fire.
